          <actionDate>2016-05-10</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p> <b>Clarifying Amendment to Provide Terrorism Victims Equity Act or the CAPTIVE Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Terrorism Risk Insurance Act of 2002 regarding the blocked assets of a terrorist party which shall be subject to execution or attachment in aid of execution in order to satisfy a judgment based upon an act of terrorism in an action brought by or on behalf of the person obtaining the judgment.</p> <p>The bill redefines &quot;blocked asset&quot; to include any asset seized or frozen by the United States under the Foreign Narcotics Kingpin Designation Act. </p> <p>The bill also defines a &quot;person&quot; who has obtained such a judgment as a natural person who, at the time the act of terrorism was committed upon which the judgment was obtained, was:</p> <ul> <li>a national of the United States;</li> <li>a member of the U.S. Armed Forces; or</li> <li>otherwise an employee of the federal government, or of a federal government contractor, acting within the scope of employment.</li> </ul> <p>If the person described is deceased, the personal representative of the estate of that deceased person shall count as the person.</p>]]></text>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
